really important insight, that you kind of gossip while you do fieldwork. You could chat on, you and I, and talk about our children, and talk about colleagues we\rquote ve had, and I think if we, if you weren\rquote 
t doing fieldwork, and you turned the tape off, it\rquote s just rolling reciprocity. That\rquote s how you do it.  And also, well, we might be professional colleagues, we\rquote re not actually going to swap it, but if you\rquote 
re actually trying to find stuff, or if you are, literally, going through the activity of gossiping \'85 and another very important paper, another man who came, Max Gluckman\rquote s paper on gossip.  Max came and gave a version of that in 
