s always been very amiable thereafter. Indeed, I spent a long period of time as External Examiner in the Keele Department when he was Head of it, and we got on as well as you could imagine.  I\rquote ve always found, I mean, of late I\rquote 
ve found a lot of what Ronnie does, very weird and wonderful, and fairly unintelligible really. But I think }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \i\insrsid14244499 Village on the Border}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14244499  is a good book. I\rquote 
