y fair.  Rose and Saunders used to argue on the grounds that it was alphabetical chance which came first. Though there is a very convoluted paragraph about divisions of labour in there.  The other thing about the farmers project, as a whole, I don\rquote 
t know how many papers it produced, but it produced a lot \endash  some of which are fairly obscure, and I\rquote 
ll give you some examples in a moment, and some are pretty important.  We set out to get Pete and David Rose articles that would get them jobs, and they were allowed to lead on things: all four names were always on \endash  we never took anybody\rquote 
