rdon and I were never on the Essex payroll at the same time.  But I got to know Gordon because every time I was back, and I was back quite a lot, because I would see Howard, and Gordon, by then, was a mate of Howard\rquote s.  So I didn\rquote 
t know Gordon before, but I knew Mike Harloe before.  Mike and I had a past before he turned up at Essex, partly mediated by Ray, by the way.  But the rural stuff stopped, for me, as the book came out, and that sort of finishes.  Was Howard different?

